summary: MAFIA STUCKY RP PROMPT Your name is Steven Grant Rogers. You’ve gone up in Brooklyn for most of the life, had plenty of friends,...
caption:
MAFIA STUCKY RP PROMPT

Your name is Steven Grant Rogers. You’ve gone up in Brooklyn for most of the life, had plenty of friends, plenty of enemies, a good handful of fights and now your in for the fight of your life.

To recap, you’ve just returned home from serving in war and because of terrible flashbacks and moments of PTSD, it hasn’t been easy to get and hold down a job, so when the moment arose to borrow some money to keep yourself afloat, you jumped at the opportunity.

However, now your extremely late on payments and are in the process of being escorted through a very nice looking building, and into a large dimly lit office, as the two men give you one last look, they shake their heads and turn to leave, a slightly familiar voice comes from the large turned chair across from you.  

The chair turns to reveal a nicely dressed, mildly irritated looking Tony Stark, the man you borrowed the money from to begin with, and he does not look pleased. “So Rogers, you’ve really screwed the pooch here…too bad to, cause i really enjoyed that pretty face of yours”

[DM to Continue the RP, NSFW is aloud, will respond as promptly as possible]

summary: How much Ironstrange is actually in Infinity War?
title: How much Ironstrange is actually in Infinity War?
body:
Because, as we all know, there is heaps. But I wanna measure it precisely with a highly advanced points system, just so we know the exact amount. And by that I mean I’ll just point out every minute detail of their interactions and give it points based on how much I like it. So let’s begin!

+1 point for actually having them meet! The writers totally could’ve just had them never interact with each other, but instead they chose to write it so that they spend the majority of the movie together.  

+1 for “did you seriously just say ‘hitherto undreamt of’?” and +1 for “Are you seriously leaning on the Cauldron of the Cosmos?”. In fact, +1 extra, just for the fact that they are consistently able keep up with each other’s wit and snark. 

+1 for when the Cloak of Levitation slaps Tony (some say it slapped his ass, but that’s debatable) and Tony says “I’m going to allow that”. 

the entire conversation about ice cream deserves +3 points. 

+3 for all the sexual tension and eye contact. 

+0.5 for Stephen calling him a douchebag. Don’t ask me why I included it, I just did, it’s my rules, you can’t stop me. 

+1 for Stephen’s “oh great” when Tony says Steve Rogers could find Vision. This implies that he somehow knows that they’re not on speaking terms even though that doesn’t seem like the sort of thing that would be public information. I mean, sure, everyone would know that the avengers broke up, but would they really know why? I wouldn’t think so. But maybe they do. I don’t know.  

+3 for “say, Doc, you wouldn’t happen to be moving your hair, would ya?” and “not at the moment, no”. I just like that Tony’s first instinct was to look at Stephen’s hair. 

+10 for The Wink™ and +1 for Tony’s little smirk. You cannot tell me that that wasn’t at least a little bit flirtatious. 

+1 for Stephen’s “umm what are you doing?” face in the background when Tony interrupts squidward’s Ebony Maw’s little speech with “I’m sorry, Earth is closed today”. 

+0.5 for “he means get lost, Squidward”. Again, don’t ask me why. 

+2 for “dude, you’re embarrassing me in front of the wizards.” 

+1 for “kid, that’s the wizard, get on it”. Protective boyfriend. 

+1 for Tony going to save Stephen from the spaceship, even though Pepper tells him to come back. I mean, he’s probably doing it mainly to save the universe, but just let me have this okay. 

+1 for both having massive egos and arguing because Stephan won’t say thanks to Tony for saving his life. 

+10 for them never really agreeing on what to do with the Time Stone until they have a Moment™ in front of a starry night sky as Tony explains that “Thanos has been inside his head for 6 years” and that’s why they should take the fight to him. 

also +5 for this shot: 

+1 also because is it just me or does Tony seem kinda shocked/thrown off when Stephen actually listens to him? It might just be my imagination, but his body language and stuff sorta changes a little. Am I crazy? 

+1 for Stephen asking if Tony’s okay and helping him up after they crash on Titan, +1 for Tony saying “I owe you one”, and +1 for them holding each others arms for a second too long. 

+0.5 for Peter being a bit of a third wheel during almost all of their interactions. 

+1 for Stephen glancing at Tony like wtf when Drax says “Why is Gamora?” 

+1 for Tony not objecting when Mantis refers to Stephen as his friend, unlike earlier with squidward Ebony Maw. 

+3 for Tony grabbing Stephen’s arm and saying “you’re back. you’re all right” after he comes back from seeing the future. Also +1 for Stephen replying with just a soft “hi”.

+2 for Stephen looking into Tony’s eyes with a sad and heartfelt expression as he says they have a 1 in 14,000,605 chance of winning. 

+1 because “oh, yeah. you’re much more of a Thanos” definitely sounds like something Tony would say, but it’s actually Stephen’s line.

+1 for Stephen teaming up with Tony’s son, Peter, and using a combination of their powers to fight Thanos. 

+3 for Tony standing between Thanos and Stephen’s unconscious body. 

+5 for Stephen giving up the Time Stone for Tony. Now, I know what you’re thinking; he only did this because he knew that was how they were going to beat Thanos. But can I point out that every other time Thanos got an infinity stone in the movie (except for the power stone, which he already had), a character had to choose between having the stone or saving a loved one’s life. When movies show patterns like this, it’s meant to be important and isn’t just a coincidence. Why would they stop this pattern? Obviously it kinda implies that Stephen at least cares about Tony a little bit. 

+0.5 because Stephen’s line “we’re in the endgame now” kinda sounds like “we (as in ironstrange) are endgame now”. I know this one’s reaching, but I don’t care, I make the rules. 

+4 for the hard “Stark” going to a soft “Tony”. 

And that’s all, folks! The total score was 75, so you can do with that what you will. If I’ve forgotten or missed anything, feel free to add stuff at the bottom.

+1 because “oh, yeah. you’re much more of a Thanos” definitely sounds like something Tony would say, but it’s actually Stephen’s line.

+1 for Stephen teaming up with Tony’s son, Peter, and using a combination of their powers to fight Thanos. 

+3 for Tony standing between Thanos and Stephen’s unconscious body. 

+5 for Stephen giving up the Time Stone for Tony. Now, I know what you’re thinking; he only did this because he knew that was how they were going to beat Thanos. But can I point out that every other time Thanos got an infinity stone in the movie (except for the power stone, which he already had), a character had to choose between having the stone or saving a loved one’s life. When movies show patterns like this, it’s meant to be important and isn’t just a coincidence. Why would they stop this pattern? Obviously it kinda implies that Stephen at least cares about Tony a little bit. 

+0.5 because Stephen’s line “we’re in the endgame now” kinda sounds like “we (as in ironstrange) are endgame now”. I know this one’s reaching, but I don’t care, I make the rules. 

+4 for the hard “Stark” going to a soft “Tony”. 

And that’s all, folks! The total score was 75, so you can do with that what you will. If I’ve forgotten or missed anything, feel free to add stuff at the bottom.
